http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Medical-student-ends-life/article14020240.ece

A 19-year-old first year MBBS student was found hanging in his hostel room at Nehru Block of Manipal University here on Sunday.According to the Manipal police, the student was Pranjal Patak from Hyderabad, who was studying in Kasturba Medical College. Girish S.V., Inspector of Manipal Police Station, told The Hindu on Monday that the student had written a death note stating that he was bored of life and he was ending it. He had written that he alone was responsible for his death.“He was a bright student. According to his friends, he had appeared depressed in the last seven days. The matter is under investigation,” Mr. Girish said.A case has been registered.